elevator version

00:03:24.860 --> 00:03:26.780
and offer some illustrations.

00:03:26.780 --> 00:03:30.110
The elevator version
basically is this--

00:03:30.110 --> 00:03:32.660
intersectionality
reflects the reality

00:03:32.660 --> 00:03:36.470
that systems of subordination--
power, discrimination,

00:03:36.470 --> 00:03:40.520
like racism, sexism,
heterosexism, ableism--

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:44.630
are not separate and distinct
forms of discrimination.

00:03:44.630 --> 00:03:46.700
Many times they overlap.

00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:48.080
They interlock.

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:51.800
They create kinds of
problems and challenges

00:03:51.800 --> 00:03:55.010
that can't be addressed if you
think of these issues as just

00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:56.210
single issues.

00:03:56.210 --> 00:03:58.820
So it's the simple
fact that, if you just

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:02.480
experience race
discrimination as a woman,

00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:05.150
you're probably experiencing
both race and gender

00:04:05.150 --> 00:04:06.950
discrimination.

00:04:06.950 --> 00:04:09.620
And so the simple
version is just

00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:12.620
recognizing that there
are multiple forms

00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:13.590
of discrimination.

00:04:13.590 --> 00:04:16.399
Some people are subject
to more than one of them,

00:04:16.399 --> 00:04:20.550
and if your tools that you
have to identify and intervene

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:22.610
do not focus on
the intersections,

00:04:22.610 --> 00:04:26.270
you're probably not doing
much to alleviate the problem.

00:04:26.270 --> 00:04:28.810
Now that's the elevator version.

00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:33.710
